<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-508] SegmentTermEnum.next() doesn&apos;t maintain prevBuffer at end</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-508</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;When you&apos;re iterating a SegmentTermEnum and you go past the end of the docs, you end up with a state where the nextBuffer = null and the prevBuffer is the penultimate term, not the last term.  This patch fixes it.  (It&apos;s also required for my Prefetching bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-506&quot; title=&quot;Optimize Memory Use for Short-Lived Indexes (Do not load TermInfoIndex if you know the queries ahead of time)&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-506&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Index: java/org/apache/lucene/index/SegmentTermEnum.java&lt;br/&gt;
===================================================================&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8212; java/org/apache/lucene/index/SegmentTermEnum.java	(revision 382121)&lt;br/&gt;
+++ java/org/apache/lucene/index/SegmentTermEnum.java	(working copy)&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -109,6 +109,7 @@&lt;br/&gt;
   /** Increments the enumeration to the next element.  True if one exists.*/&lt;br/&gt;
   public final boolean next() throws IOException {&lt;br/&gt;
     if (position++ &amp;gt;= size - 1) &lt;/p&gt;
{
+      prevBuffer.set(termBuffer);
       termBuffer.reset();
       return false;
     }</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Lucene Trunk&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
